{
  "texts": [
    "Some schemes may compromise certain security attributes, while others manage to strike a balance.",
    "Therefore, the challenge of minimizing the size of group signatures and keys while maintaining security remains an important area of research for the future.",
    "Ring signature, as a special form of group signature, was proposed by Rivest and others in 2001 (Rivest et al. 2001), addressing the issue of achieving anonymous digital signatures.",
    "What sets it apart from group signatures is that in ring signatures, there is no group manager.",
    "Verification of the signature does not disclose the specific members' identities."
  ]
}